text: Mohammad Al-Subaie (, born 20 October 1995) is a Saudi Arabian professional footballer who plays as a winger for Pro League side Al-Raed. ==Career== Al- Subaie began his career at the youth team of Al-Ettifaq. On 12 August 2016, Al-Subaie joined MS League side Al-Nahda on loan for the 2016–17 season. On 22 April 2018, Al-Subaie renews his contract with Al-Ettifaq for 4 year . On 29 May 2019, Another athlete, the International Commission for the Control of Doping, caught another athlete, Al-Ittifaq player Mohamed Al-Subaie, who received a one-year suspension from May 9. on 18 August 2020, Al-Subaie joined Al-Raed. ==References== == External links == * Category:1995 births Category:Living people Category:Saudi Arabian footballers Category:Ettifaq FC players Category:Al-Nahda Club (Saudi Arabia) players Category:Al-Raed FC players Category:Saudi Professional League players Category:Prince Mohammad bin Salman League players Category:Association football wingers
